        "# PD Model Training – Quantum (QSVM / VQC)\n",
        "\n",
        "**Purpose:** Train hybrid quantum-classical PD models on the same engineered LendingClub features as the XGBoost notebook. We use **PennyLane** (or Qiskit) simulators only (CPU, no real hardware). Models: **QSVM** (quantum kernel) and/or **VQC** (Variational Quantum Classifier / QNN). Compare AUC-ROC, F1, and KS-drift vs the classical XGBoost baseline.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Runtime:** **Auto-detected** — **Colab** / **Kaggle** = clone repo and install deps; **local** = CPU-only (e.g. i5-11500, 16GB). **Critical design:** VQC with data re-uploading and small init; blend with XGBoost; **model snapshot** = `.pkl`; **report** = cell outputs (Colab download only).\n",
        "\n",
        "**Input:** `data/credit_risk_pd/LendingClub/processed/lendingclub_engineered.parquet` (run notebook 01 first). **Dependencies:** `pennylane`, `pennylane-sf`."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 1. Load engineered data (same as notebook 02a)\n",
        "\n",
        "Same best-practice split and preprocessing as 02a; class imbalance is preserved in the data (no SMOTE). Quantum models use the same feature set and time-based train/val/test split."
      ]
    },
    {
